The paper discusses the security and privacy challenges in vehicular communication systems, which are related to cryptography (cs.CR), networking (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), control systems (cs.SY), and cyber security (cs.CY). The focus on identity and credential management suggests a stronger connection to cryptography and networking, hence the higher likelihood of cs.CR and cs.NI. However, the paper also touches upon standardization and industry adoption, which may involve software engineering and control systems, as well as cyber security concerns.
